                            <comment id="15046999" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 16:01:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks!  Yes, we have been a bit lax in keeping the xsd up to date.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15047059" author="erikkemperman" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 16:53:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No problem. Just noticed the shutdownHook attribute is also missing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is validating the xml an uncommon thing to do?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15047088" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 17:20:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If it was common I suspect we would have gotten more complaints. It has been out of date for quite a while. The issue is that there is only so much validation you can actually do since you can add your own custom plugins with their own attributes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15047128" author="erikkemperman" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 17:41:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fair enough. I only got to looking at it because Eclipse complains about xml without dtd or schema. Guess I&apos;ll keep my modified xsd around until you guys get around to this. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15047431" author="garydgregory" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 20:41:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In Git master. Please verify and close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15047468" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 21:08:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Gary, I think more changes are needed for the Script, ScriptRef and ScriptFile tags, the CronTriggerPolicy, the Delete element in DefaultRolloverStrategy and perhaps the FileWatcher. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15047512" author="garydgregory" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 21:39:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Probably, I just addressed the patch. No time ATM...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15048643" author="erikkemperman" created="Wed, 9 Dec 2015 13:06:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For what it&apos;s worth, the current XSD also doesn&apos;t allow the &quot;append&quot; attribute to Appender elements.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15049142" author="garydgregory" created="Wed, 9 Dec 2015 18:31:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Feel free to attach a diff file to this ticket based on git master. The prevous diff did not apply cleanly FWIW.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
